Bluetongue [BT], [North Macedonia]
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] Fri 10 Jul 2020 from Dr Zoran Atanasov, Director Food and Veterinary Agency, [Skopje, North Macedonia]

Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 5 Jul 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 9 Jul 2020
Report date: 10 Jul 2020
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 27 Feb 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Greshnica, Makedosni Brod, Brod
Date of start of the outbreak: 5 Jul 2020
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep, goats / 466 / 9 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep, goats / 1.93 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: After reporting to the official veterinarian that there were animals with clinical signs of bluetongue, samples were taken from all animals with clinical signs. The same disease, bluetongue, was confirmed in 2014 on this farm. The National Laboratory under Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, Skopje, is sequencing and comparing the current strain with the strain that occurred in 2014. Note from the World Animal Health Information and Analysis Department: As per WAHIS Notification Procedures, the date of last occurrence (i.e. [27 Feb 2015]) is the date when the last event for the reported disease was declared resolved.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, screening, quarantine, zoning, disinfection, disinfestation, vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: control of vectors, vector surveillance

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, Veterinary Institute (national laboratory) / Sheep, goats / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 9 Jul 2020 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

